00:08:23,494 --> 00:08:25,633
I didn't know you worked at Nipong Naepong.

254
00:08:26,233 --> 00:08:28,232
- Did you go by a nickname then? - No.

255
00:08:28,233 --> 00:08:30,102
Servers at restaurants like that had English nicknames like Ashley.

256
00:08:30,103 --> 00:08:31,232
Do you have an English name?

257
00:08:31,233 --> 00:08:32,402
It's Sarah.

258
00:08:32,403 --> 00:08:33,973
- Sarah? - Shout out?

259
00:08:34,133 --> 00:08:35,403
- Shut it. - Sarah.

260
00:08:35,573 --> 00:08:37,202
- Shout out? - Shut it right now.

261
00:08:37,203 --> 00:08:38,273
No.

262
00:08:38,343 --> 00:08:40,342
- Did you mean, "shout out?" - It's Sarah.

263
00:08:40,343 --> 00:08:41,842
- Sarah. - That's my English name.

264
00:08:41,843 --> 00:08:43,143
- What's yours? - Why Sarah?

265
00:08:43,243 --> 00:08:45,113
- My English name? Ken. - Yes.

266
00:08:45,353 --> 00:08:46,612
- Ken. - Really?

267
00:08:46,613 --> 00:08:48,483
- What kind of can? - I can do it. Ken.

268
00:08:49,183 --> 00:08:50,482
- Ken. Yes. - It's really Ken?

269
00:08:50,483 --> 00:08:51,752
- I see. - Really?

270
00:08:51,753 --> 00:08:52,992
Isn't it cool? Ken.

271
00:08:52,993 --> 00:08:55,293
- Ken Jeong. - Yes, Ken Jeong.

272
00:08:55,993 --> 00:08:57,122
Do you have one, Yeon Shik?

273
00:08:57,123 --> 00:08:58,262
- I do. - What is it?

274
00:08:58,263 --> 00:08:59,433
Brandon.

275
00:09:00,433 --> 00:09:02,302
- Do you know "Bread Barbershop?" - Brandon.

276
00:09:02,303 --> 00:09:03,603
- Brandon. - "Brandon Barbershop."

277
00:09:03,733 --> 00:09:04,962
- Brandon. - What?

278
00:09:04,963 --> 00:09:06,632
- That's a good name. - Brandon.

279
00:09:06,633 --> 00:09:08,302
- Brandon. - Isn't that the best name so far?

280
00:09:08,303 --> 00:09:09,942
- Gosh, that's so funny. - Brandon.

281
00:09:09,943 --> 00:09:11,602
- What's yours? - What?

282
00:09:11,603 --> 00:09:12,643
James.

283
00:09:15,073 --> 00:09:17,242
- James. - My gosh.

284
00:09:17,243 --> 00:09:18,582
- My gosh. - James.

285
00:09:18,583 --> 00:09:20,282
- I didn't know. - Right. James.

286
00:09:20,283 --> 00:09:21,312
- Right. - It doesn't suit him.

287
00:09:21,313 --> 00:09:22,722
Is J from your name, Jae Suk?

288
00:09:22,723 --> 00:09:24,422
- James. - James.

289
00:09:24,423 --> 00:09:26,122
- James. - Jae Suk.

290
00:09:26,123 --> 00:09:27,853
(The national MC sounds rather too pretentious.)

291
00:09:27,993 --> 00:09:30,022
- Cheers. - Cheers.

292
00:09:30,023 --> 00:09:31,862
- Why aren't you eating DCC? - Well, I can.

293
00:09:31,863 --> 00:09:32,932
- Okay. - Is it okay if I eat it?

294
00:09:32,933 --> 00:09:34,632
- Of course. We had two too. - Yes.

295
00:09:34,633 --> 00:09:35,703
I...

296
00:09:36,803 --> 00:09:38,832
- I'll grab it. - I bet you can eat it in one bite.

297
00:09:38,833 --> 00:09:40,302
- No, I can't. - Really?

298
00:09:40,303 --> 00:09:42,873
- I have a tiny mouth. - This is tasty. Seriously.

299
00:09:43,243 --> 00:09:45,073
She's pretending to have a small mouth.

300
00:09:45,673 --> 00:09:47,942
Look at you pretending when you can eat it in one bite.

301
00:09:47,943 --> 00:09:49,413
Hey, that looks weirder.

302
00:09:50,013 --> 00:09:51,143
It's good.

303
00:09:51,543 --> 00:09:52,713
My gosh. She's...

304
00:09:53,613 --> 00:09:55,723
My gosh. What? He's so sweet.

305
00:09:55,783 --> 00:09:56,923
- Thank you. - Okay.

306
00:09:57,583 --> 00:09:58,652
This is tasty.

307
00:09:58,653 --> 00:09:59,993
(The foodie is devouring DCC.)

308
00:10:00,653 --> 00:10:01,923
She's eating it with gusto.

309
00:10:02,093 --> 00:10:04,123
- She loves food. - Yes.

310
00:10:04,693 --> 00:10:05,793
Seriously.

311
00:10:05,993 --> 00:10:08,163
- Wait. Isn't the mirror too small? - It's perfect.

312
00:10:08,293 --> 00:10:10,263
- A princess mirror. - A princess mirror?

313
00:10:10,603 --> 00:10:11,963
I doubt you can see your whole face in it.

314
00:10:13,533 --> 00:10:15,843
(Scowling)

315
00:10:16,103 --> 00:10:17,573
- I mean... - She looks really upset.

316
00:10:17,803 --> 00:10:18,943
What's wrong with him?

317
00:10:19,043 --> 00:10:21,712
- My face is as small as this. - You can't see your whole face.

318
00:10:21,713 --> 00:10:23,113
You keep pushing it far back.

319
00:10:24,143 --> 00:10:25,513
My face is as small as this.

320
00:10:25,653 --> 00:10:27,052
- It's the powder on the skin. - I see. This?

321
00:10:27,053 --> 00:10:28,053
- I'm eating. - Ye Eun. Let's show...

322
00:10:28,054 --> 00:10:29,482
your teeth on three.

323
00:10:29,483 --> 00:10:31,483
- One, two... - Why would you ask me to do that?

324
00:10:32,083 --> 00:10:33,393
You're so awful.

325
00:10:36,223 --> 00:10:38,592
- You sound way too angry. - Your attitude is awful.

326
00:10:38,593 --> 00:10:41,093
It looks like you think everyone here today is lame.

327
00:10:41,263 --> 00:10:43,703
- You guys are all lame. - You're lame too.

328
00:10:44,363 --> 00:10:45,602
- You too. - You're lame too.

329
00:10:45,603 --> 00:10:46,702
You're lame too.

330
00:10:46,703 --> 00:10:47,873
(They're only disappointed in each other.)

331
00:10:47,973 --> 00:10:49,772
- But she's changed a bit. - She's on many TV shows now.

332
00:10:49,773 --> 00:10:50,872
In what ways?

333
00:10:50,873 --> 00:10:54,243
- When she was a rookie... - Tell us.

334
00:10:54,673 --> 00:10:57,643
Back in the day, my career had peaked.

335
00:10:57,843 --> 00:11:01,453
I started from the bottom and made it to the top.

336
00:11:01,783 --> 00:11:03,322
It was crazy.

337
00:11:03,323 --> 00:11:04,422
- I was at the height of my career. - I know.

338
00:11:04,423 --> 00:11:05,523
So know your place.

339
00:11:05,923 --> 00:11:07,592
Know your place.

340
00:11:07,593 --> 00:11:08,723
Of course.

341
00:11:09,623 --> 00:11:10,963
Tell us.

342
00:11:11,163 --> 00:11:12,593
It was pretty crazy back then.

343
00:11:12,893 --> 00:11:15,133
- But now, she's quite famous. - Gosh.

344
00:11:15,233 --> 00:11:17,732
I was waiting for her in my car earlier.

345
00:11:17,733 --> 00:11:19,302
I was happy to see her, so I went to her car...

346
00:11:19,303 --> 00:11:20,373
and called her.

347
00:11:20,803 --> 00:11:23,143
She rolled down her window.

348
00:11:23,203 --> 00:11:24,842
She rolled down her window.

349
00:11:24,843 --> 00:11:26,472
- She only put her hand out. - Sang Hun.

350
00:11:26,473 --> 00:11:28,442
"Hey, Sang Hun." That's what she did.

351
00:11:28,443 --> 00:11:29,483
- Sang Hun. - So...

352
00:11:29,883 --> 00:11:31,143
- Ye Eun. - Sang Hun.

353
00:11:31,243 --> 00:11:32,983
- Ye Eun. - Sang Hun.

354
00:11:33,513 --> 00:11:34,753
So I held her hand.

355
00:11:34,783 --> 00:11:35,822
(Exaggerating the scene)

356
00:11:35,823 --> 00:11:37,153
- Ye Eun, have you been well? - Sang Hun.

357
00:11:38,483 --> 00:11:40,952
- So... - He will get the wrong idea.

358
00:11:40,953 --> 00:11:42,563
- He'll get the wrong idea? - Yes, right.

359
00:11:42,823 --> 00:11:44,322
- Listen. - He should get the wrong idea?

360
00:11:44,323 --> 00:11:45,462
- No. - I should get the wrong idea.

361
00:11:45,463 --> 00:11:47,162
- It doesn't matter... - No.

362
00:11:47,163 --> 00:11:48,902
- if he gets the wrong idea. - No, he got the wrong idea.

363
00:11:48,903 --> 00:11:50,232
- He got the wrong idea. - What?

364
00:11:50,233 --> 00:11:52,903
Let me explain. I was putting on my shoes.

365
00:11:53,573 --> 00:11:56,403
- I had to say hello right away. - You were trying to say hello.

366
00:11:56,543 --> 00:11:59,512
- Come on. You know what I'm like. - What if it was Jae Suk, not me?

367
00:11:59,513 --> 00:12:01,312
- I would've done the same thing. - You'd do it to Jae Suk too?

368
00:12:01,313 --> 00:12:02,743
That's your inferiority complex.

369
00:12:04,683 --> 00:12:06,382
- You'd do it to Jae Suk too? - That's your inferiority complex.

370
00:12:06,383 --> 00:12:08,113
(Inferiority complex)

371
00:12:08,923 --> 00:12:11,322
(Sang Hun has an inferiority complex.)

372
00:12:11,323 --> 00:12:13,252
- Inferiority complex? - See? She makes me cry.

373
00:12:13,253 --> 00:12:14,723
Inferiority complex.

374
00:12:15,193 --> 00:12:17,022
- Inferiority complex. - I cry so easily, to begin with.

375
00:12:17,023 --> 00:12:18,062
(Her senior takes a big hit.)

376
00:12:18,063 --> 00:12:19,462
- Inferiority complex. - Yes.

377
00:12:19,463 --> 00:12:21,693
- Inferiority complex. - I haven't changed.

378
00:12:22,363 --> 00:12:24,533
She said he had an inferiority complex on Lunar New Year's Day.

379
00:12:25,203 --> 00:12:27,473
We ended the talk with Sang Hun's inferiority complex.

380
00:12:28,403 --> 00:12:30,043
- He has an inferiority complex. - My gosh. She got me.

381
00:12:30,373 --> 00:12:31,573
Happy New Year.

382
00:12:31,773 --> 00:12:33,673
- Okay. We should get going now. - Yes.

383
00:12:33,873 --> 00:12:35,213
- Yes. - Let's take a look.

384
00:12:35,983 --> 00:12:37,412
(Surprised)

385
00:12:37,413 --> 00:12:39,453
- The first Whenever Guests. - That's gotten pretty long.

386
00:12:39,513 --> 00:12:40,652
- We have a lot of cards now. - Yes.

387
00:12:40,653 --> 00:12:41,653
Wait. We have...

388
00:12:41,654 --> 00:12:43,253
- four Whenever Guests. - What?

389
00:12:43,383 --> 00:12:44,982
"Kim Se Jin, Ok Ji Hyung,"

390
00:12:44,983 --> 00:12:47,193
"Kim Sung Pil, and Baek Sung Wook."

391
00:12:47,393 --> 00:12:48,893
"Burning flames,"

392
00:12:49,093 --> 00:12:50,623
"freezing water,"

393
00:12:51,093 --> 00:12:52,792
"and rooftops at dizzying heights."

394
00:12:52,793 --> 00:12:54,933
"You just name it, and we're ready to roll."

395
00:12:55,293 --> 00:12:57,302
- Gosh, I figured it out. - "To become superheroes..."

396
00:12:57,303 --> 00:12:58,933
"to rescue the residents of Ilsan,"

397
00:12:59,133 --> 00:13:01,503
"we're leveling up through various experiences."

398
00:13:01,933 --> 00:13:04,342
- I wonder what they do. - "I'd love to make a memory..."

399
00:13:04,343 --> 00:13:06,773
"that will make our heart beat and give us a dopamine rush."

400
00:13:07,213 --> 00:13:08,512
- Firefighters. - Firefighters.

401
00:13:08,513 --> 00:13:09,613
- Are they firefighters? - Yes.

402
00:13:09,943 --> 00:13:11,413
- Do you think so? - I'm 100 percent sure.

403
00:13:11,643 --> 00:13:13,953
- "Burning flames, freezing water," - "Flames."

404
00:13:14,083 --> 00:13:15,212
"and rooftops."

405
00:13:15,213 --> 00:13:16,752
- They come down from the rooftops. - They're ready to roll.

406
00:13:16,753 --> 00:13:18,423
- "Ready to roll." - Let's go. What's our meeting time?

407
00:13:18,853 --> 00:13:20,352
- We must be there by noon. - We must go now.

408
00:13:20,353 --> 00:13:21,353
- What time is it? - Yes.

409
00:13:21,354 --> 00:13:23,393
The bus will arrive in four minutes.

410
00:13:23,663 --> 00:13:24,893
Really? We must hurry.

411
00:13:25,423 --> 00:13:26,963
But we have to cross the street.

412
00:13:27,163 --> 00:13:28,263
- We must get on the bus from there. - Really?

413
00:13:28,463 --> 00:13:29,833
- There? - Yes.

414
00:13:31,003 --> 00:13:33,973
Do you remember the old days? On Lunar New Year's Day,

415
00:13:34,233 --> 00:13:35,532
my kids...

416
00:13:35,533 --> 00:13:38,002
- They wore hanbok, right? - used to wear hanbok. Gosh.

417
00:13:38,003 --> 00:13:39,412
- People rarely wear hanbok now. - Right.

418
00:13:39,413 --> 00:13:41,412
- Right. - You actually see more hanbok...

419
00:13:41,413 --> 00:13:43,513
- At Gyeongbokgung Palace. - You see it at palaces.

420
00:13:44,113 --> 00:13:45,882
Back then, it felt festive.

421
00:13:45,883 --> 00:13:47,453
- I smell something tasty. - Wait.

422
00:13:47,613 --> 00:13:48,813
- What smell? - Wait.

423
00:13:49,023 --> 00:13:50,452
- This is from Nipong Naepong. - It smells like...

424
00:13:50,453 --> 00:13:51,582
- Isn't it from Nipong Naepong? - No.

425
00:13:51,583 --> 00:13:53,053
- It smells like jjamppong. - Yes, it's jjamppong.

426
00:13:53,223 --> 00:13:54,393
- I smell Chinese food. - Jjamppong.

427
00:13:55,393 --> 00:13:56,793
- You're spot on. - It smells like jjamppong.

428
00:13:57,723 --> 00:14:00,063
- I can smell the smoky flavor. - Yes. I smell it too.

429
00:14:00,563 --> 00:14:03,362
- Gosh, it smells so good. - They're getting ready for lunch.

430
00:14:03,363 --> 00:14:04,703
- Right. - No wonder why I smelled pizza.

431
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:06,202
(As they walk while enjoying delicious smells...)

432
00:14:06,203 --> 00:14:07,203
Pizza.

433
00:14:07,533 --> 00:14:08,933
- Bus 99. - Yes.

434
00:14:09,643 --> 00:14:10,773
Bus 99. This one.

435
00:14:11,843 --> 00:14:13,473
Gosh, they must make the font bigger.

436
00:14:14,343 --> 00:14:16,412
- Isn't it too small, Yeon Seok? - What's too small?

437
00:14:16,413 --> 00:14:18,442
- It's... - The font is too small for him.

438
00:14:18,443 --> 00:14:20,112
- No, I can read it. - You know?

439
00:14:20,113 --> 00:14:21,213
- You can read everything? - Gosh.

440
00:14:21,413 --> 00:14:22,853
Do you think you can read this?

441
00:14:23,153 --> 00:14:24,183
What?

442
00:14:24,953 --> 00:14:26,253
- "Gimpobon-dong." - It's small.

443
00:14:26,593 --> 00:14:30,522
Yeon Seok has been showing symptoms of presbyopia now.

444
00:14:30,523 --> 00:14:32,022
Stop bringing that up.

445
00:14:32,023 --> 00:14:33,693
- Why every week... - Has it been three years?

446
00:14:34,093 --> 00:14:35,193
- Why... - Three years?

447
00:14:35,833 --> 00:14:37,363
His eyes are getting worse every year.

448
00:14:38,303 --> 00:14:39,303
They worsen dramatically overnight.

449
00:14:39,304 --> 00:14:40,802
- Right. - It's like falling off a cliff.

450
00:14:40,803 --> 00:14:41,972
- These changes are quite dramatic. - That's how it goes.

451
00:14:41,973 --> 00:14:43,243
But there's nothing you can do.

452
00:14:43,443 --> 00:14:44,542
- Bus 99. - What?

453
00:14:44,543 --> 00:14:45,813
- It's here. - Yes, that's the one.

454
00:14:46,513 --> 00:14:47,572
- Hello. - Hi.

455
00:14:47,573 --> 00:14:48,913
- Hello. - Hello.

456
00:14:51,313 --> 00:14:53,183
- You didn't say it. - I didn't.

457
00:14:53,853 --> 00:14:55,312
- I'm sorry. - You already knew, right?

458
00:14:55,313 --> 00:14:56,423
I'm going to sit down.

459
00:14:56,783 --> 00:14:57,823
- In the back? - My gosh.

460
00:14:59,823 --> 00:15:01,352
(Sitting down next to Jae Suk)

461
00:15:01,353 --> 00:15:02,463
- There aren't enough seats. - Oh, no.

462
00:15:03,023 --> 00:15:04,723
- No, there are some seats. - Right.

463
00:15:06,033 --> 00:15:07,093
I'm shy.

464
00:15:07,563 --> 00:15:09,233
Shouldn't all the cameramen go over there?

465
00:15:09,403 --> 00:15:10,533
They're all heading there.

466
00:15:10,833 --> 00:15:11,903
Is it my inferiority complex talking?

467
00:15:14,473 --> 00:15:16,303
(There are seats here.)

468
00:15:17,073 --> 00:15:18,542
(Spotting a seat)

469
00:15:18,543 --> 00:15:20,573
- Go sit. Your legs are weak. - What?

470
00:15:22,073 --> 00:15:23,142
You go ahead.

471
00:15:23,143 --> 00:15:24,483
- Sit down. - I'm young.

472
00:15:25,543 --> 00:15:26,653
I'm young.

473
00:15:27,313 --> 00:15:28,652
Then I'll go.

474
00:15:28,653 --> 00:15:29,653
(Chuckling)

475
00:15:32,453 --> 00:15:33,593
I'm young.

476
00:15:34,153 --> 00:15:36,722
Okay. My gosh. I should be quiet.

477
00:15:36,723 --> 00:15:37,922
(Everyone except for the youngster sits down.)

478
00:15:37,923 --> 00:15:38,963
Wait.

479
00:15:40,263 --> 00:15:41,692
We're letting her stand by herself?

480
00:15:41,693 --> 00:15:42,703
(Laughing)

481
00:15:43,503 --> 00:15:44,702
- Ye Eun. - What is this?

482
00:15:44,703 --> 00:15:46,802
- I kept asking Ye Eun... - She chose not to sit.

483
00:15:46,803 --> 00:15:47,972
How can we treat our guest like this?

484
00:15:47,973 --> 00:15:49,602
- She chose not to sit down. - She said no.

485
00:15:49,603 --> 00:15:50,603
I asked her first.

486
00:15:52,143 --> 00:15:53,213
Do I look pretty on camera?

487
00:15:53,943 --> 00:15:56,413
(Making sure she gets her close-up shot)

488
00:15:56,613 --> 00:15:57,943
This is airing on Lunar New Year's Day.

489
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,213
My grandma will watch this.

490
00:16:01,213 --> 00:16:03,182
Grandma. Ms. Kim Chang Sung.

491
00:16:03,183 --> 00:16:04,183
(You're watching, right?)

492
00:16:05,653 --> 00:16:06,952
Ye Eun is the youngest.

493
00:16:06,953 --> 00:16:08,623
Sir, bring the camera here.

494
00:16:09,093 --> 00:16:10,423
Come over here.

495
00:16:10,523 --> 00:16:11,663
We have a seat here.

496
00:16:15,133 --> 00:16:18,033
