501
00:16:38,223 --> 00:16:39,552
I'm getting off at this stop.

502
00:16:39,553 --> 00:16:41,593
(I'm getting off at this stop.)

503
00:16:44,593 --> 00:16:46,133
They look good together.

504
00:16:46,263 --> 00:16:47,432
- You know? - Yes.

505
00:16:47,433 --> 00:16:48,692
(Different vibes on the same bus)

506
00:16:48,693 --> 00:16:50,403
- That will air on TV. - Right.

507
00:16:51,103 --> 00:16:53,772
I was a huge fan of "Hospital Playlist."

508
00:16:53,773 --> 00:16:54,833
Really?

509
00:16:55,003 --> 00:16:56,642
(Shy)

510
00:16:56,643 --> 00:16:58,003
What was the name of my character?

511
00:16:59,613 --> 00:17:02,343
(Chuckling since she doesn't remember it)

512
00:17:03,313 --> 00:17:04,443
Kwak Jun Pal.

513
00:17:06,013 --> 00:17:09,322
(When Ye Eun and Jun Pal are sharing laughs...)

514
00:17:09,323 --> 00:17:11,283
- Jung Seok had his second baby. - Right.

515
00:17:12,153 --> 00:17:14,993
- My gosh. Of course. - He's over the moon.

516
00:17:15,253 --> 00:17:17,793
I saw a photo of his second baby.

517
00:17:18,893 --> 00:17:21,733
It's rare for a newborn to look that pretty.

518
00:17:22,263 --> 00:17:24,033
- She's a beauty. - Really?

519
00:17:24,833 --> 00:17:26,733
- I envy him. - It's good that she's healthy.

520
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:29,073
He has 2 daughters and I have 3 sons.

521
00:17:29,643 --> 00:17:31,143
- You have three sons? - Yes.

522
00:17:31,643 --> 00:17:33,572
- They're pretty big now, right? - Yes.

523
00:17:33,573 --> 00:17:34,613
How old is your youngest?

524
00:17:34,743 --> 00:17:36,182
He will be in third grade now.

525
00:17:36,183 --> 00:17:37,583
I see. Well...

526
00:17:38,483 --> 00:17:41,713
My eldest will start middle school.

527
00:17:41,853 --> 00:17:44,323
I need to see how his adolescent phase will go.

528
00:17:45,153 --> 00:17:47,593
I had a pretty intense adolescent phase too.

529
00:17:47,753 --> 00:17:48,823
- You too? - Yes.

530
00:17:49,193 --> 00:17:52,093
I don't know why. But I just wanted to run back then.

531
00:17:52,993 --> 00:17:54,632
I don't know, but I wanted to run.

532
00:17:54,633 --> 00:17:56,363
- So you rode the bicycle. - Yes, I did.

533
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:58,663
I used to ride the bicycle.

534
00:17:58,963 --> 00:18:00,973
We have to play games to give out presents.

535
00:18:01,673 --> 00:18:03,143
- This stop is... - My gosh. It's...

536
00:18:03,303 --> 00:18:04,843
Wait. Where are we?

537
00:18:04,973 --> 00:18:06,013
We missed our stop.

538
00:18:06,913 --> 00:18:09,543
Oh, no. We were busy chatting. Hold on.

539
00:18:09,683 --> 00:18:10,982
My gosh, Yeon Seok.

540
00:18:10,983 --> 00:18:12,683
- Oh, no. - Come on.

541
00:18:13,413 --> 00:18:14,653
Guys, we missed it.

542
00:18:14,883 --> 00:18:16,023
Back then...

543
00:18:16,983 --> 00:18:18,083
What?

544
00:18:18,353 --> 00:18:19,493
We must get off here.

545
00:18:20,053 --> 00:18:21,952
- Let's get off here. - What...

546
00:18:21,953 --> 00:18:23,063
Let's get off here and walk a bit.

547
00:18:24,793 --> 00:18:26,332
We went one stop too far.

548
00:18:26,333 --> 00:18:27,733
- We went one stop too far. - Gosh, what do we do?

549
00:18:27,963 --> 00:18:31,132
- How can you miss our stop? - How can you miss it?

550
00:18:31,133 --> 00:18:32,902
You were standing by the door. What were you two talking about?

551
00:18:32,903 --> 00:18:34,672
What were you two talking about?

552
00:18:34,673 --> 00:18:35,972
- We were talking and... - He totally...

553
00:18:35,973 --> 00:18:37,272
- fell for my charms. - What were you talking about?

554
00:18:37,273 --> 00:18:38,342
Did you really fall...

555
00:18:38,343 --> 00:18:39,412
- for her charms? - I mean...

556
00:18:39,413 --> 00:18:41,612
He said that he enjoyed watching my shows.

557
00:18:41,613 --> 00:18:42,682
You suddenly want her, right?

558
00:18:42,683 --> 00:18:44,613
- She's charming. - Yes, I am.

559
00:18:44,883 --> 00:18:46,312
- She must've charmed you. - Seriously.

560
00:18:46,313 --> 00:18:49,983
- So many celebrities like her. - That's it.

561
00:18:51,083 --> 00:18:52,893
- Cooking Maniac, - Right.

562
00:18:53,093 --> 00:18:54,623
Mickey Kwang Soo, Yoo Hee Kwan,

563
00:18:55,593 --> 00:18:56,723
and Yang Se Chan.

564
00:18:57,393 --> 00:18:58,923
- They have a similar look. - No.

565
00:18:59,223 --> 00:19:00,692
- No. - I'm serious.

566
00:19:00,693 --> 00:19:01,693
- Okay. - Those guys...

567
00:19:01,694 --> 00:19:03,702
Those guys like Ye Eun for real.

568
00:19:03,703 --> 00:19:05,103
I'm popular as you know.

569
00:19:06,533 --> 00:19:07,972
Jae Suk and I were talking...

570
00:19:07,973 --> 00:19:09,403
- Ji Ye Eun. - about the adolescent phase.

571
00:19:09,803 --> 00:19:11,772
- Hello. - We kept...

572
00:19:11,773 --> 00:19:13,012
- "Ji Ye Eun." - What?

573
00:19:13,013 --> 00:19:14,213
You know that I'm popular, right?

574
00:19:14,673 --> 00:19:16,013
- What? - They said my name.

575
00:19:16,843 --> 00:19:19,482
- Maybe they said, "Get lost." - No.

576
00:19:19,483 --> 00:19:20,652
- "Ji Ye Eun." - No.

577
00:19:20,653 --> 00:19:21,983
- They said, "Get lost." - It might be Ilsan Fire Station.

578
00:19:23,253 --> 00:19:25,353
- I see. We were right. - This is the place?

579
00:19:25,553 --> 00:19:27,393
- It's a fire station. - We were right.

580
00:19:27,593 --> 00:19:28,693
We're going to a fire station.

581
00:19:28,853 --> 00:19:30,022
Right.

582
00:19:30,023 --> 00:19:32,762
I've never been inside a fire station.

583
00:19:32,763 --> 00:19:33,932
(We're ready to roll.)

584
00:19:33,933 --> 00:19:35,892
- Wait. It said we should go... - Don't point out the obvious.

585
00:19:35,893 --> 00:19:38,763
to the cafeteria on the first floor.

586
00:19:39,303 --> 00:19:40,603
There's a cafeteria on the first floor.

587
00:19:41,473 --> 00:19:43,803
- I see. It was a fire station. - A fire station.

588
00:19:43,903 --> 00:19:45,643
I've never been inside a fire station.

589
00:19:46,013 --> 00:19:48,112
- What? - There's "A Firefighter's Prayer."

590
00:19:48,113 --> 00:19:49,213
"Dear Almighty."

591
00:19:49,583 --> 00:19:51,543
"When I'm called to perform my duty,"

592
00:19:51,583 --> 00:19:53,682
"give me strength to save a life..."

593
00:19:53,683 --> 00:19:55,813
"no matter how strong the flames may be."

594
00:19:56,953 --> 00:19:58,952
"Help me protect a child..."

595
00:19:58,953 --> 00:19:59,953
(Help me protect a child before it is too late.)

596
00:19:59,954 --> 00:20:01,252
"before it is too late."

597
00:20:01,253 --> 00:20:03,063
"Help me save elders, shivering in fear."

598
00:20:03,823 --> 00:20:05,022
- "And..." - "If I meet my fate..."

599
00:20:05,023 --> 00:20:06,132
"at your will,"

600
00:20:06,133 --> 00:20:09,062
"I ask that you watch over my wife and my family."

601
00:20:09,063 --> 00:20:10,063
- Gosh. - Oh, my.

602
00:20:10,203 --> 00:20:11,603
What an emotional poem.

603
00:20:12,973 --> 00:20:16,642
Before responding to emergencies,

604
00:20:16,643 --> 00:20:18,172
- they recite this poem. - This is what they tell themselves.

605
00:20:18,173 --> 00:20:19,572
- Then they set out. - Yes.

606
00:20:19,573 --> 00:20:20,573
(Reminding themselves with their hard work and sacrifices)

607
00:20:21,773 --> 00:20:23,242
There's a cafeteria.

608
00:20:23,243 --> 00:20:24,942
(Who are the Whenever Guests they will meet right away?)

609
00:20:24,943 --> 00:20:26,983
- Hello. - Gosh.

610
00:20:27,413 --> 00:20:29,182
- You were all here. - Hello.

611
00:20:29,183 --> 00:20:30,422
- Hello. - Nice to meet you.

612
00:20:30,423 --> 00:20:32,182
- My gosh. - Hello.

613
00:20:32,183 --> 00:20:35,153
Se Jin, Ji Hyung, Sung Pil, and Sung Wook.

614
00:20:36,193 --> 00:20:38,562
(Day...)

615
00:20:38,563 --> 00:20:39,933
(or night)

616
00:20:41,533 --> 00:20:43,732
(Fires, water,)

617
00:20:43,733 --> 00:20:46,603
(land, sky)

618
00:20:47,103 --> 00:20:48,872
(Heroes who fight to keep us safe...)

619
00:20:48,873 --> 00:20:50,842
(wherever and whenever)

620
00:20:50,843 --> 00:20:52,673
(Photos of the Whenever Guests)

621
00:20:53,243 --> 00:20:54,272
- Nice to meet you. - My gosh.

622
00:20:54,273 --> 00:20:56,082
- Hello. - Hello.

623
00:20:56,083 --> 00:20:57,982
(The Whenever Guests are four firefighters on active duty.)

624
00:20:57,983 --> 00:21:00,852
Is this your lunchtime? Tell us about your spare time.

625
00:21:00,853 --> 00:21:03,152
- It's our lunchtime now. - Right. It's our lunchtime.

626
00:21:03,153 --> 00:21:05,822
We're all from the same batch. So we were here...

627
00:21:05,823 --> 00:21:07,622
- We were just chatting. - Yes, we were chatting.

628
00:21:07,623 --> 00:21:09,862
- We were just conversing. - You trained in the same batch?

629
00:21:09,863 --> 00:21:10,962
- Yes. - Yes.

630
00:21:10,963 --> 00:21:12,763
(They've been working for 6 years as firefighters.)

631
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:16,332
All of you have a notebook.

632
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:18,232
This notebook is replacing our turnout gear...

633
00:21:18,233 --> 00:21:20,003
- when we're on duty. - Right.

634
00:21:20,133 --> 00:21:21,172
- Really? - Yes.

635
00:21:21,173 --> 00:21:23,143
- How? - Let me explain.

636
00:21:23,443 --> 00:21:26,442
The four of us used to do fieldwork.

637
00:21:26,443 --> 00:21:29,042
Then we were transferred to desk duty at Ilsan Fire Station.

638
00:21:29,043 --> 00:21:30,043
- To desk duty. - Yes.

639
00:21:30,044 --> 00:21:32,783
- You don't do fieldwork now. - Right.

640
00:21:33,013 --> 00:21:34,712
We're on support duty.

641
00:21:34,713 --> 00:21:36,222
- We're on support duty. - We're on support duty.

642
00:21:36,223 --> 00:21:39,422
Then could you tell us some of the tasks you handle?

643
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:42,052
At our fire station, we are in charge of many policies.

644
00:21:42,053 --> 00:21:44,292
We also come up with countermeasures for fire prevention and safety.

645
00:21:44,293 --> 00:21:46,992
There are fire extinguishers and flame detectors.

646
00:21:46,993 --> 00:21:49,292
They are called residential fire prevention systems.

647
00:21:49,293 --> 00:21:52,902
Currently, I'm overseeing a project where I supply these systems...

648
00:21:52,903 --> 00:21:54,402
to financially disadvantaged communities...

649
00:21:54,403 --> 00:21:55,873
and older apartment buildings.

650
00:21:56,573 --> 00:21:59,873
I handle complaints and requests the fire station receives.

651
00:22:00,343 --> 00:22:02,012
I oversee the management...

652
00:22:02,013 --> 00:22:04,043
of dangerous facilities like gas stations.

653
00:22:04,583 --> 00:22:06,113
(Safety seminars)

654
00:22:06,613 --> 00:22:08,113
(Equipment management)

655
00:22:09,723 --> 00:22:12,223
(They're fighting in their own way to prevent accidents.)

656
00:22:12,893 --> 00:22:14,592
(It's as busy inside the office as it is out in the field.)

657
00:22:14,593 --> 00:22:17,392
All these projects sound challenging.

658
00:22:17,393 --> 00:22:19,022
But handling complaints is tough.

659
00:22:19,023 --> 00:22:21,432
- You have to resolve the issues. - Right.

660
00:22:21,433 --> 00:22:24,202
- It must be a stressful job. - Right.

661
00:22:24,203 --> 00:22:28,172
What are some difficult complaints you came across so far?

662
00:22:28,173 --> 00:22:31,572
The toughest part of this job is when I catch them breaking the law.

663
00:22:31,573 --> 00:22:34,772
- We have to charge them a fine. - You do.

664
00:22:34,773 --> 00:22:36,582
Most of them are good people.

665
00:22:36,583 --> 00:22:39,012
- But a few people... - Right.

666
00:22:39,013 --> 00:22:41,282
tend to get quite upset.

667
00:22:41,283 --> 00:22:43,052
- They're sensitive. - They get sensitive.

668
00:22:43,053 --> 00:22:46,922
Right. Back in the day, traffic police officers...

669
00:22:46,923 --> 00:22:48,352
would conduct DUI checkpoints.

670
00:22:48,353 --> 00:22:49,892
A good number of drivers would argue with them.

671
00:22:49,893 --> 00:22:51,263
- They get out of the car first. - That was common.

672
00:22:52,093 --> 00:22:53,892
"Hold on. Which batch are you from?"

673
00:22:53,893 --> 00:22:54,893
(Starting a skit)

674
00:22:54,894 --> 00:22:57,062
"You served, right?" They try to find a connection.

675
00:22:57,063 --> 00:22:58,232
(Acting out the scene from the old days)

676
00:22:58,233 --> 00:22:59,603
You do a lot of skits.

677
00:23:00,103 --> 00:23:01,533
I thought she'd get up.

678
00:23:02,433 --> 00:23:03,542
- I don't have that experience. - You thought she'd join you.

679
00:23:03,543 --> 00:23:04,543
(Their joint skit fell through.)

680
00:23:04,544 --> 00:23:06,103
You thought she'd join you.

681
00:23:06,413 --> 00:23:08,542
I expected her to say, "Honey, calm down."

682
00:23:08,543 --> 00:23:09,612
But she didn't.

683
00:23:09,613 --> 00:23:11,882
(Her comedy colleague is disappointed.)

684
00:23:11,883 --> 00:23:13,153
- I thought you'd do that. - I see.

685
00:23:13,313 --> 00:23:15,552
Which one of you applied to the show?

686
00:23:15,553 --> 00:23:16,722
- He did. - Me.

687
00:23:16,723 --> 00:23:18,152
What made you write to our show?

688
00:23:18,153 --> 00:23:19,452
We were assigned to different stations...

689
00:23:19,453 --> 00:23:21,752
- Right. - for our first post.

690
00:23:21,753 --> 00:23:23,162
We were scattered across different stations.

691
00:23:23,163 --> 00:23:24,792
Then we were all assigned here.

692
00:23:24,793 --> 00:23:28,232
On top of that, we were all transferred to desk duty.

693
00:23:28,233 --> 00:23:29,862
- I thought it was interesting. - Indeed.

694
00:23:29,863 --> 00:23:32,602
We wanted to make a great memory together, so I wrote the letter.

695
00:23:32,603 --> 00:23:36,072
Then I'm assuming that the four of you are quite close.

696
00:23:36,073 --> 00:23:37,703
- Yes. - We're very close.

697
00:23:38,473 --> 00:23:39,743
We go on trips together.

698
00:23:39,813 --> 00:23:41,473
- Really? - Yes.

699
00:23:41,613 --> 00:23:43,112
Where did you go recently?

700
00:23:43,113 --> 00:23:45,782
The four of us wanted to go skiing...

701
00:23:45,783 --> 00:23:48,583
on a trip. But he's married.

702
00:23:49,413 --> 00:23:50,482
I have a child.

703
00:23:50,483 --> 00:23:52,482
He couldn't join us. But the three of us...

704
00:23:52,483 --> 00:23:54,353
recently went skiing and had a great time bonding.

705
00:23:55,023 --> 00:23:56,152
- That's great. - But...

706
00:23:56,153 --> 00:23:59,862
I'm sure you each have your own reason...

707
00:23:59,863 --> 00:24:01,292
you became a firefighter.

708
00:24:01,293 --> 00:24:03,062
Could you tell us what made you choose this path?

709
00:24:03,063 --> 00:24:05,332
I was in 11th grade.

710
00:24:05,333 --> 00:24:07,202
The study cafe I went caught fire.

711
00:24:07,203 --> 00:24:09,673
- Oh, no. - I called 911.

712
00:24:09,903 --> 00:24:11,942
I knocked on the doors and told them there was a fire.

713
00:24:11,943 --> 00:24:13,972
I got them to evacuate from the building.

714
00:24:13,973 --> 00:24:16,512
- Gosh. - That was a good thing you did.

715
00:24:16,513 --> 00:24:19,652
Afterward, I got into a different line of work.

716
00:24:19,653 --> 00:24:20,952
Then I found myself...

717
00:24:20,953 --> 00:24:22,982
remembering those cool firefighters...

718
00:24:22,983 --> 00:24:25,022
- from that accident. - You wanted to be like them.

719
00:24:25,023 --> 00:24:26,222
- I remembered them. - You remembered them.

720
00:24:26,223 --> 00:24:29,352
Yes. I wanted to be like them. That's how I got here.

721
00:24:29,353 --> 00:24:30,393
(I wanted to be like them.)

722
00:24:30,863 --> 00:24:33,432
I first became interested in this career...

723
00:24:33,433 --> 00:24:35,032
after watching "Heartbeat."

724
00:24:35,033 --> 00:24:36,703
- Yes, I remember the show. - Yes.

725
00:24:36,763 --> 00:24:38,332
- It was an SBS show. - That's right.

726
00:24:38,333 --> 00:24:39,532
When I was watching it,

727
00:24:39,533 --> 00:24:41,102
I didn't know much about...

728
00:24:41,103 --> 00:24:43,502
what firefighters' responsibilities were.

729
00:24:43,503 --> 00:24:46,172
They rescued people in need and felt proud.

730
00:24:46,173 --> 00:24:48,612
When I watched them save lives,

731
00:24:48,613 --> 00:24:50,642
I thought that was my calling.

732
00:24:50,643 --> 00:24:52,642
The moment I watched it, I felt it in my bones.

733
00:24:52,643 --> 00:24:55,252
My gosh. That's so...

734
00:24:55,253 --> 00:24:56,522
That's when I felt it.

735
00:24:56,523 --> 00:24:57,953
(Amazing determination)

736
00:24:58,323 --> 00:25:00,422
(Their reasons may be all different,)

737
00:25:00,423 --> 00:25:02,392
(but they were appointed for the same purpose.)

738
00:25:02,393 --> 00:25:03,393
(Reliable Batch Crew of Firefighters)

739
00:25:03,394 --> 00:25:05,562
The people you start your career with...

740
00:25:05,563 --> 00:25:06,592
- are special. - Of course.

741
00:25:06,593 --> 00:25:09,392
Yes. Anyway,

742
00:25:09,393 --> 00:25:11,462
this episode will air on Lunar New Year's Day.

743
00:25:11,463 --> 00:25:13,232
Let's nail it today.

744
00:25:13,233 --> 00:25:16,002
Let's do a good job and complete the missions.

745
00:25:16,003 --> 00:25:17,743
(It's time to do the mission, but at a different location.)

746
00:25:17,903 --> 00:25:19,202
It's cold here.

747
00:25:19,203 --> 00:25:20,212
(Going to a more spacious place)

748
00:25:20,213 --> 00:25:21,313
What's this?

749
00:25:21,443 --> 00:25:23,513
This gym is quite big.

750
00:25:23,913 --> 00:25:25,712
What's going on? All right.

751
00:25:25,713 --> 00:25:27,453
- Ye Eun, could you roll the dice? - Sure.

752
00:25:27,683 --> 00:25:30,552
We're getting bonus chances based on the number you roll.

753
00:25:30,553 --> 00:25:32,182
- The firefighters can join us too. - Let's go!

754
00:25:32,183 --> 00:25:33,823
- You got this! - Yes.

755
00:25:34,523 --> 00:25:36,122
- Go ahead. - This is a lot of pressure.

756
00:25:36,123 --> 00:25:37,123
Throw it.

757
00:25:37,493 --> 00:25:38,562
- Let's go! - You got this!

758
00:25:38,563 --> 00:25:39,692
You got this!

759
00:25:39,693 --> 00:25:41,493
(How many bonus coupons will they get?)

760
00:25:43,333 --> 00:25:44,503
There it is.

761
00:25:45,863 --> 00:25:47,572
We still got one.

762
00:25:47,573 --> 00:25:50,142
- Not bad. - That's good enough.

763
00:25:50,143 --> 00:25:51,242
Great.

764
00:25:51,243 --> 00:25:54,013
Let's check the present for Round One.

765
00:25:55,673 --> 00:25:57,712
