00:43:11,360 --> 00:43:12,499
It looks good.

1288
00:43:12,500 --> 00:43:14,530
The place has about 500 reviews.

1289
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:16,229
- Yeon Seok... - Yes?

1290
00:43:16,230 --> 00:43:17,599
You depend on reviews, don't you?

1291
00:43:17,600 --> 00:43:18,939
- He must love delicious food. - You do.

1292
00:43:18,940 --> 00:43:20,540
- He loves delicious food. - Totally.

1293
00:43:21,040 --> 00:43:22,509
The place seems small.

1294
00:43:22,510 --> 00:43:23,710
(Excited about the must-eat place)

1295
00:43:23,810 --> 00:43:25,740
Back when I was in Daehak-ro,

1296
00:43:26,110 --> 00:43:28,610
there was this dumpling place in Myeongnyun-dong.

1297
00:43:28,780 --> 00:43:29,979
- In Myeongnyun-dong? - Yes.

1298
00:43:29,980 --> 00:43:31,650
It was right before Myeongnyun-dong.

1299
00:43:31,920 --> 00:43:33,819
The dumplings were 10 for 1 dollar.

1300
00:43:33,820 --> 00:43:35,119
- The dumplings? - Yes.

1301
00:43:35,120 --> 00:43:36,249
- It was that cheap? - Yes.

1302
00:43:36,250 --> 00:43:38,350
- With just 2 dollars, I was full. - Why was it...

1303
00:43:38,960 --> 00:43:40,619
- Those dumplings were amazing. - so cheap?

1304
00:43:40,620 --> 00:43:41,620
- What's more, the dumplings... - That's...

1305
00:43:41,621 --> 00:43:42,689
- were handmade. - super cheap.

1306
00:43:42,690 --> 00:43:43,990
- Handmade dumplings? - That's so cheap.

1307
00:43:44,330 --> 00:43:46,760
I remember eating...

1308
00:43:47,300 --> 00:43:49,299
those steaming hot dumplings to this day.

1309
00:43:49,300 --> 00:43:52,269
That steam from steamed buns and dumplings...

1310
00:43:52,270 --> 00:43:54,439
- Dumplings. - when cooked outside in winter.

1311
00:43:54,440 --> 00:43:55,469
I know, right?

1312
00:43:55,470 --> 00:43:58,009
- I love dumplings. - It's a great marketing strategy.

1313
00:43:58,010 --> 00:43:59,180
- You can't just pass by. - Exactly.

1314
00:44:01,340 --> 00:44:02,410
I have a runny nose.

1315
00:44:03,310 --> 00:44:05,520
(But the weather is...)

1316
00:44:06,320 --> 00:44:07,720
(Groaning)

1317
00:44:09,750 --> 00:44:11,489
The wind is insane.

1318
00:44:11,490 --> 00:44:12,659
- It's... - It's a biting wind.

1319
00:44:12,660 --> 00:44:14,389
(Cutting wind in minus 9°C weather)

1320
00:44:14,390 --> 00:44:16,260
There's also a North Korean restaurant.

1321
00:44:16,590 --> 00:44:18,029
- Enough. - I know the place.

1322
00:44:18,030 --> 00:44:19,199
Don't we have to walk a bit?

1323
00:44:19,200 --> 00:44:20,960
- To the right. - I know that spot.

1324
00:44:21,130 --> 00:44:22,169
It's really famous.

1325
00:44:22,170 --> 00:44:23,469
- Is it? - It's famous.

1326
00:44:23,470 --> 00:44:26,070
- Shall we go there? - Stop it. Let's just get dumplings.

1327
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:29,469
- The cook is from North Korea. - Really?

1328
00:44:29,470 --> 00:44:31,710
I feel like we're in North Korea. It's freezing cold.

1329
00:44:32,180 --> 00:44:34,080
- We're here. - Isn't this Hamkyeong Province?

1330
00:44:34,310 --> 00:44:36,380
- Dumplings. - Dumplings.

1331
00:44:36,580 --> 00:44:37,880
- Is this the place? - Shall we?

1332
00:44:38,050 --> 00:44:39,149
- It's just like the place... - Shall we?

1333
00:44:39,150 --> 00:44:40,250
- we talked about. - Shall we?

1334
00:44:40,580 --> 00:44:41,720
There aren't enough seats.

1335
00:44:42,050 --> 00:44:44,019
(But there aren't enough seats.)

1336
00:44:44,020 --> 00:44:45,559
- The tables are too small. - Takeaway...

1337
00:44:45,560 --> 00:44:47,020
- Maybe just takeaway. - Hi.

1338
00:44:47,490 --> 00:44:49,189
- It's small. - I see. Keep up the great work.

1339
00:44:49,190 --> 00:44:50,489
- Bye. - Happy New Year.

1340
00:44:50,490 --> 00:44:51,860
- Happy New Year. - Happy New Year.

1341
00:44:52,030 --> 00:44:53,400
- Happy New Year. - We would've loved some dumplings.

1342
00:44:54,130 --> 00:44:55,870
What a bummer.

1343
00:44:56,900 --> 00:44:58,030
We made that long trip.

1344
00:44:58,230 --> 00:45:01,539
Look at our untidy hair.

1345
00:45:01,540 --> 00:45:03,369
(Everyone is a mess.)

1346
00:45:03,370 --> 00:45:04,510
Really.

1347
00:45:04,840 --> 00:45:06,540
It's... Sang Hun.

1348
00:45:06,880 --> 00:45:08,440
- Sang Hun. - Yes?

1349
00:45:08,780 --> 00:45:10,849
- What happened? - Where did Jae Suk go?

1350
00:45:10,850 --> 00:45:12,020
What happened to us?

1351
00:45:12,250 --> 00:45:14,120
- Where's Jae Suk? - Even Yeon Seok.

1352
00:45:14,420 --> 00:45:16,289
- We're a complete mess. - To the North Korean place or no?

1353
00:45:16,290 --> 00:45:17,520
- Yes, let's go. - At this rate,

1354
00:45:17,720 --> 00:45:20,220
- we might end up in North Korea. - Let's go.

1355
00:45:21,490 --> 00:45:22,989
Turn right, and we should be there.

1356
00:45:22,990 --> 00:45:24,829
- Really? - Before we know it,

1357
00:45:24,830 --> 00:45:26,430
- we've walked to Pyongyang. - Wait.

1358
00:45:26,860 --> 00:45:28,359
- Where are we? - You know,

1359
00:45:28,360 --> 00:45:31,000
I had no idea we had crossed the Military Demarcation Line.

1360
00:45:31,130 --> 00:45:32,540
How did this happen?

1361
00:45:33,540 --> 00:45:35,339
- It's the green light. - The light is green.

1362
00:45:35,340 --> 00:45:38,140
- I can't run. - My legs are shaking.

1363
00:45:38,240 --> 00:45:39,480
I could run earlier.

1364
00:45:40,140 --> 00:45:43,310
Guys, isn't this like walking across the entire country?

1365
00:45:44,010 --> 00:45:47,080
This is fun. Yeon Seok, I'm having fun.

1366
00:45:47,820 --> 00:45:50,020
- The show is exciting. - Yes, exciting.

1367
00:45:50,990 --> 00:45:52,120
It's exciting.

1368
00:45:53,320 --> 00:45:54,460
- Sang Hun. - I can smell galbi.

1369
00:45:55,120 --> 00:45:57,190
- It smells delicious. - Short rib soup sounds good too.

1370
00:45:57,790 --> 00:45:58,899
We're here.

1371
00:45:58,900 --> 00:46:00,129
(They arrive at the North Korean restaurant.)

1372
00:46:00,130 --> 00:46:01,299
This place is famous.

1373
00:46:01,300 --> 00:46:02,900
I think I've heard of it.

1374
00:46:03,400 --> 00:46:05,570
- It looks good. - Sang Hun...

1375
00:46:06,170 --> 00:46:08,169
Have you been here before, Sang Hun?

1376
00:46:08,170 --> 00:46:09,439
- Yes, a while ago. - Hi.

1377
00:46:09,440 --> 00:46:10,539
- Hi. - Welcome.

1378
00:46:10,540 --> 00:46:12,380
- Gosh. - I'll sit inside.

1379
00:46:12,910 --> 00:46:14,010
It's freezing cold.

1380
00:46:14,280 --> 00:46:15,380
It is, right?

1381
00:46:16,580 --> 00:46:17,710
There are so many options.

1382
00:46:18,350 --> 00:46:20,020
I want Pyongyang naengmyeon.

1383
00:46:20,480 --> 00:46:22,119
- Cold? - Yes, cold.

1384
00:46:22,120 --> 00:46:24,450
- How about with bulgogi? - I'm in.

1385
00:46:24,790 --> 00:46:26,789
- Let's share Pyongyang naengmyeon. - Two bulgogi.

1386
00:46:26,790 --> 00:46:28,590
- One rolled dumpling. - Isn't it one per person?

1387
00:46:29,090 --> 00:46:30,190
- One per person? - Yes.

1388
00:46:30,330 --> 00:46:32,960
- One Pyongyang naengmyeon for two. - One for two?

1389
00:46:33,260 --> 00:46:34,700
- One for... - Two for one.

1390
00:46:34,900 --> 00:46:36,700
- One per person. - One per person?

1391
00:46:36,930 --> 00:46:37,930
That sounds a lot.

1392
00:46:37,931 --> 00:46:40,270
- We'd like to order. - Four Pyongyang naengmyeon.

1393
00:46:40,400 --> 00:46:41,600
One rolled dumpling.

1394
00:46:42,010 --> 00:46:44,010
- Three bulgogi. - Two bulgogi.

1395
00:46:45,070 --> 00:46:46,179
(The foodie made the order.)

1396
00:46:46,180 --> 00:46:47,340
How nice.

1397
00:46:47,580 --> 00:46:49,950
Hearing old songs is nice.

1398
00:46:50,710 --> 00:46:53,649
(What now? My heart is acting up)

1399
00:46:53,650 --> 00:46:54,950
Modern lyrics aren't like the old ones.

1400
00:46:55,490 --> 00:46:56,720
- There's no hesitation. - No.

1401
00:46:56,890 --> 00:46:58,119
- "What now?" - No.

1402
00:46:58,120 --> 00:46:59,189
People just go for it these days.

1403
00:46:59,190 --> 00:47:01,690
- True. - "What now?" doesn't exist anymore.

1404
00:47:02,030 --> 00:47:03,959
Songs like "WE SHOULD'VE BEEN FRIENDS..."

1405
00:47:03,960 --> 00:47:05,159
- by Gummy don't exist anymore. - No.

1406
00:47:05,160 --> 00:47:06,499
- No friends. - "Should've been?"

1407
00:47:06,500 --> 00:47:07,830
- No way. - No way.

1408
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:09,100
"Get lost" is the trend now.

1409
00:47:10,600 --> 00:47:12,270
- Exactly. Bang Bang Bang - No.

1410
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:14,240
- Bang Bang Bang - Bang Bang Bang

1411
00:47:14,400 --> 00:47:16,310
"BANG BANG BANG" is so old now.

1412
00:47:16,810 --> 00:47:19,340
Gosh, I don't know any recent songs.

1413
00:47:20,010 --> 00:47:21,279
"BANG BANG BANG" is old now.

1414
00:47:21,280 --> 00:47:22,650
(That song is from 10 years ago.)

1415
00:47:24,980 --> 00:47:26,820
I can't help but space out.

1416
00:47:27,880 --> 00:47:29,019
(The warmth makes them zone out.)

1417
00:47:29,020 --> 00:47:31,389
Zoning out is one of the best things in the world.

1418
00:47:31,390 --> 00:47:32,489
- Really? - Yes.

1419
00:47:32,490 --> 00:47:35,060
I heard it's when the brain gets a break.

1420
00:47:35,460 --> 00:47:37,890
You two barely talked during "Saturday Night Live Korea," right?

1421
00:47:38,230 --> 00:47:39,330
There's no time to talk.

1422
00:47:39,460 --> 00:47:42,300
For "Saturday Night Live Korea," we gather at 9am...

1423
00:47:42,470 --> 00:47:43,730
- True. - and start our meeting.

1424
00:47:44,030 --> 00:47:46,569
- Brainstorming begins. - Yes.

1425
00:47:46,570 --> 00:47:47,700
- There's no time to chat. - It's tiresome.

1426
00:47:47,800 --> 00:47:49,910
Skits are tough.

1427
00:47:50,070 --> 00:47:51,369
- Totally. - I agree.

1428
00:47:51,370 --> 00:47:52,940
- You have to make it funny. - Exactly.

1429
00:47:53,440 --> 00:47:55,140
- Making it funny is hard. - It's hard.

1430
00:47:55,310 --> 00:47:57,109
- If you fail to make it funny... - Fail to make it funny...

1431
00:47:57,110 --> 00:47:59,050
- You feel ashamed. - Exactly, you become...

1432
00:47:59,280 --> 00:48:02,020
- depressed. - For real. You get depressed.

1433
00:48:02,250 --> 00:48:04,319
Your peers say, "Don't worry. It was funny."

1434
00:48:04,320 --> 00:48:06,260
No one says that in "Saturday Night Live Korea."

1435
00:48:06,360 --> 00:48:07,389
- Really? - Right away?

1436
00:48:07,390 --> 00:48:09,459
- No. - Your role changes right away.

1437
00:48:09,460 --> 00:48:11,390
Exactly. Your role changes instantly,

1438
00:48:11,930 --> 00:48:13,030
and that's brutal.

1439
00:48:13,400 --> 00:48:14,460
Exactly.

1440
00:48:14,830 --> 00:48:17,170
- But that's part of the fun. - True.

1441
00:48:18,170 --> 00:48:20,540
I'm excited. I haven't had Pyongyang naengmyeon in ages.

1442
00:48:20,940 --> 00:48:22,569
- What was that? - I haven't had it in ages.

1443
00:48:22,570 --> 00:48:23,570
(The foodie is excited.)

1444
00:48:23,571 --> 00:48:26,039
- The mustard... - I don't add mustard.

1445
00:48:26,040 --> 00:48:27,339
No, if you do...

1446
00:48:27,340 --> 00:48:28,409
You're not supposed to add...

1447
00:48:28,410 --> 00:48:29,480
- mustard to Pyongyang naengmyeon. - Why?

1448
00:48:29,780 --> 00:48:32,480
What? Pyongyang naengmyeon should be enjoyed as it is.

1449
00:48:32,650 --> 00:48:35,179
How about a little vinegar and mustard?

1450
00:48:35,180 --> 00:48:37,319
No, you have to savor the original flavor.

1451
00:48:37,320 --> 00:48:39,589
- The original flavor? - Do you have a certificate?

1452
00:48:39,590 --> 00:48:42,329
- No, I just... - Right?

1453
00:48:42,330 --> 00:48:43,830
- No, right? - No.

1454
00:48:44,190 --> 00:48:45,729
So, you have a certificate,

1455
00:48:45,730 --> 00:48:47,160
and you have an inferiority complex.

1456
00:48:47,830 --> 00:48:49,230
An inferiority complex.

1457
00:48:49,430 --> 00:48:51,000
A certificate and an inferiority complex.

1458
00:48:51,570 --> 00:48:55,200
When you gave that speech at the awards ceremony,

1459
00:48:55,240 --> 00:48:57,740
what made you sob like that?

1460
00:48:58,440 --> 00:49:01,340
(The Excellence Award acceptance speech at the 2025 awards ceremony)

1461
00:49:03,680 --> 00:49:05,109
Thank you for loving...

1462
00:49:05,110 --> 00:49:06,120
(Sobbing)

1463
00:49:09,150 --> 00:49:10,989
(I'm so nervous.)

1464
00:49:10,990 --> 00:49:14,460
(She stepped down while bawling her eyes out.)

1465
00:49:14,790 --> 00:49:17,659
When I look at the members of "Running Man,"

1466
00:49:17,660 --> 00:49:18,660
it makes me cry.

1467
00:49:18,860 --> 00:49:20,500
Because they remind you of how hard you worked together?

1468
00:49:21,130 --> 00:49:22,200
Not that.

1469
00:49:23,130 --> 00:49:24,130
Why not?

1470
00:49:24,131 --> 00:49:25,739
Because they called me so often...

1471
00:49:25,740 --> 00:49:27,940
when I was going through something.

1472
00:49:28,140 --> 00:49:29,569
- They cheered you up. - Yes.

1473
00:49:29,570 --> 00:49:32,279
Jae Suk also...

1474
00:49:32,280 --> 00:49:34,110
called me a lot.

1475
00:49:34,240 --> 00:49:35,610
I told her to just shut up and do it.

1476
00:49:36,680 --> 00:49:38,410
Yes, something like that.

1477
00:49:38,510 --> 00:49:39,749
- "Shut your mouth..." - "Just do it?"

1478
00:49:39,750 --> 00:49:40,979
"and just do it."

1479
00:49:40,980 --> 00:49:42,149
- Yes. - Your bulgogi is ready.

1480
00:49:42,150 --> 00:49:43,189
Look at that.

1481
00:49:43,190 --> 00:49:45,919
- I love bulgogi. - With water parsley. It looks good.

1482
00:49:45,920 --> 00:49:47,019
(Pyongyang-style bulgogi with a bunch of water parsley)

1483
00:49:47,020 --> 00:49:48,190
The water parsley looks great.

1484
00:49:49,160 --> 00:49:51,130
It looks kind of bland.

1485
00:49:51,260 --> 00:49:54,299
Everything in North Korea is bland, sir.

1486
00:49:54,300 --> 00:49:55,569
Are you from North Korea?

1487
00:49:55,570 --> 00:49:57,970
No, not at all.

1488
00:49:59,100 --> 00:50:01,169
- I was born in Seoul. - He's...

1489
00:50:01,170 --> 00:50:03,209
He must have tried a lot of North Korean foods.

1490
00:50:03,210 --> 00:50:05,580
- Right. - No, I am from Seoul.

1491
00:50:06,080 --> 00:50:08,039
- Will you use the tongs to flip it? - Yes.

1492
00:50:08,040 --> 00:50:10,009
I am sorry, but I know what I am doing,

1493
00:50:10,010 --> 00:50:11,950
so please don't tell me what to do.

1494
00:50:12,880 --> 00:50:14,119
- Okay. - Rolled dumplings.

1495
00:50:14,120 --> 00:50:15,180
Thank you.

1496
00:50:15,790 --> 00:50:16,849
(Pyongan-style rolled dumplings)

1497
00:50:16,850 --> 00:50:17,950
I love these.

1498
00:50:18,420 --> 00:50:20,490
- Right. - It's good.

1499
00:50:20,790 --> 00:50:21,889
It's so good.

1500
00:50:21,890 --> 00:50:24,330
(The dumplings she's been looking for)

1501
00:50:26,530 --> 00:50:28,159
The skin is really thin.

1502
00:50:28,160 --> 00:50:29,469
No, it's skinless.

1503
00:50:29,470 --> 00:50:30,699
- It's skinless. - It's skinless.

1504
00:50:30,700 --> 00:50:32,469
- Oh, it's skinless? - They just roll the filling.

1505
00:50:32,470 --> 00:50:34,040
- Just the filling. - It's so good.

1506
00:50:34,800 --> 00:50:36,169
(Pyongyang naengmyeon to go with dumplings)

1507
00:50:36,170 --> 00:50:37,270
Awesome.

1508
00:50:38,010 --> 00:50:39,209
(The noodle lover goes to work.)

1509
00:50:39,210 --> 00:50:41,240
- They gave us so many. - It's neat.

1510
00:50:42,280 --> 00:50:44,380
I wanted hot soup, but naengmyeon is also good.

1511
00:50:45,310 --> 00:50:47,549
(Wrap this in that.)

1512
00:50:47,550 --> 00:50:48,650
Eat them together?

1513
00:50:48,950 --> 00:50:50,020
They're delicious.

1514
00:50:51,950 --> 00:50:53,089
Try it.

1515
00:50:53,090 --> 00:50:54,090
(The foodie begins eating seriously.)

1516
00:50:54,091 --> 00:50:55,760
(She tries the noodles first.)

1517
00:50:56,460 --> 00:50:58,489
This tastes...

1518
00:50:58,490 --> 00:50:59,529
(Finishing with 3 spoonfuls of soup)

1519
00:50:59,530 --> 00:51:00,630
It's good.

1520
00:51:00,830 --> 00:51:02,160
- Right? - Yes.

1521
00:51:03,070 --> 00:51:04,929
I actually wanted hot soup,

1522
00:51:04,930 --> 00:51:06,240
- but I am enjoying eating... - Yes.

1523
00:51:06,340 --> 00:51:07,440
- this cold Pyongyang naengmyeon. - Totally.

1524
00:51:07,740 --> 00:51:10,569
How did we get here from talking about rice cake soup?

1525
00:51:10,570 --> 00:51:11,570
(The irony of eating cold noodles after talking about rice cake soup)

1526
00:51:11,571 --> 00:51:12,780
It's pretty interesting.

1527
00:51:13,740 --> 00:51:15,440
Aren't you on a tour around the provinces?

1528
00:51:15,910 --> 00:51:17,580
No, that's over.

1529
00:51:17,610 --> 00:51:19,320
- It's over? - I'm on a new piece.

1530
00:51:19,680 --> 00:51:21,619
- What's the new one? - It's called "Swing Days."

1531
00:51:21,620 --> 00:51:23,289
- Okay. - It's about Dr. New Il Han.

1532
00:51:23,290 --> 00:51:26,019
The one who established Yuhan Corporation.

1533
00:51:26,020 --> 00:51:27,120
It's based on his story.

1534
00:51:27,290 --> 00:51:30,460
Yu Jun Sang is also in it.

1535
00:51:30,690 --> 00:51:33,529
And Kim Gun Woo.

1536
00:51:33,530 --> 00:51:35,299
- Kim Gun Woo? - Aren't you from the same school?

1537
00:51:35,300 --> 00:51:37,969
- He was my senior. - Gun Woo.

1538
00:51:37,970 --> 00:51:40,040
